pops a few european balloons this is a good critique of the assumptions made by eurocentric historians over the years about the superiority of europe as compared to the inferiority of the rest of the world . blaut effectively examines and explodes each theory dispassionately but thoroughly . finally he comes up with his own explanation for european success since 1492 : america . europe 's & quot ; discovery & quot ; of and exploitation of north and south america gave it the wherewithall it needed to overtake and surpass the rest of the world . a well written , well documented assessment which deserves a place beside the great divergence and reorient , among others